Question 11:
What is public static void main(string[]args) in Java?

Answer:
It is the main Java method, and is the entry point of all Java programs.

public:  it is the access modifier of the main method. It specifies who can access this method. The term “public” makes it available to all the classes.
static: At the start, there is no object class present, therefore the main method is static, which makes the JVM load the class into memory and call the main method.
void: In Java every program is required to provide a return type. However the main() method does not return anything hence its return type is void.
main: It informs the JVM that this is the main Java method.
string[]args: This is the java command line argument. It is an array of type java.lang.Stringclass. The name of the string array is args, and the user can rename it accordingly.
Question 12:
