Answer:
Java string pool is a pool of strings that is stored in a memory heap. It is also known as String Intern Pool or String Constant Pool.

There are two ways to create a string in JAVA:

Using string literal
Using new keyword
Question 13:
What is shallow copy and deep copy in JAVA?

Answer:
Shallow Copy: When a shadow copy is implemented, the copied object copies the “original” object, however it does not copy the inner objects.

If the original object contains a reference variable, then the copied object will refer to the same object to which the original was referring to. Therefore a change in the original object will reflect the same in the shallow copy.

Therefore the shallow copy is dependent on the original object.

Deep Copy: When a deep copy is implemented, the copied object copies the original object. It also calls the clone() method which then makes copies of the references that the original object contained.

Thus any change in the original will not be reflected on the deep copy making it independent of the original object.

